<h1>Normalizer representative (property)</h1>
<p>This page documents an <a href="https://www.optimade.org/">OPTIMADE</a> <a href="https://schemas.optimade.org/#definitions">Property Definition</a>. See <a href="https://schemas.optimade.org/">https://schemas.optimade.org/</a> for more information.</p>
<p><strong>ID: <a href="https://schemas.anyterial.se/defs/v0.1/properties/symmetry/normalizer_representative"><code>https://schemas.anyterial.se/defs/v0.1/properties/symmetry/normalizer_representative</code></a></strong><br>
<strong>Definition name:</strong> <code>normalizer_representative</code></p>
<p><strong>Property name:</strong> Normalizer representative<br>
<strong>Description:</strong> One listed representative of a Euclidean or affine normalizer operation or coset.
In affine-normalizer tables the representative is taken modulo the space group, so it should be read as one representative of an equivalence class rather than as the only operation in that class.
Bounded affine-normalizer tables enumerate only the finite candidate set documented by the generator.<br>
<strong>Type:</strong> dictionary  </p>
<p><strong>Requirements/Conventions</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>It MUST be a dictionary with the following keys:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>rmat</strong>: OPTIONAL; Exact 3x3 matrix.
  Linear part when the representative is expressed as a same-setting affine operation.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>tvec</strong>: OPTIONAL; List of 3 Fractions (String).
  Translation part when the representative is expressed as a same-setting affine operation.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>pmat</strong>: OPTIONAL; Exact 3x3 matrix.
  Matrix part when the representative is expressed as a basis or setting transform.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>pvec</strong>: OPTIONAL; List of 3 Fractions (String).
  Origin shift when the representative is expressed as a basis or setting transform.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>xyz</strong>: OPTIONAL; String.
  Coordinate expression for display and debugging.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>compatible_systems</strong>: OPTIONAL; List of strings.
  Crystal metric systems for which a bounded affine candidate is compatible.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>operation_kind</strong>: OPTIONAL; String.
  Generator classification of the operation.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>normalizer_kind</strong>: OPTIONAL; String.
  Classification of the normalizer contribution.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><code>{"rmat": [["-1", "0", "0"], ["0", "-1", "0"], ["0", "0", "1"]], "tvec": ["0", "0", "0"], "xyz": "-x,-y,z", "rmat_det": 1, "rmat_is_orthogonal": true, "compatible_systems": ["monoclinic", "orthorhombic"]}</code></li>
</ul>
